cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY

The paper discusses the Spectre and Meltdown vulnerabilities in modern microprocessors and their impact on performance. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also measures the impact on workloads relevant to high-performance computing (HPC) systems, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
